text: Saint-Hymetière-sur-Valouse is a commune in the Jura department in Bourgogne- Franche-Comté in eastern France. It was established on 1 January 2019 by merger of the former communes of Chemilla (the seat), Cézia, Lavans-sur- Valouse and Saint-Hymetière.Arrêté préfectoral 11 December 2018 ==See also== *Communes of the Jura department ==References== * INSEE statistics Category:Communes of Jura (department)
title: Saint-Hymetière-sur-Valouse
